@PaigeHHarvey yeah, I checked with my GP and they'd be happy to take it, but it's always a risk that if I move my new GP won't and I'll have to start paying privately, which would effectively mean I would come off medication. God I hate the state of healthcare in this country
@JustGayla_TTV TLDR if you suspect, get on it as soon as physically possible

@JustGayla_TTV Thanks Gayla. Honestly it's horrific and stressful to navigate. I've been on the NHS waitlist for nearly 12 months and haven't even had a letter to say they've received my referral, so I'm trying to figure out the right to choose side but it's literally hell

@PaigeHHarvey in true ADHD fashion I'm looking into this endless void of stress and finding it VERY difficult not to just bypass the whole thing and credit card a private diagnosis which in the long term is a VERY BAD IDEA

@PaigeHHarvey I hadn't thought of that, thank you Panne I'm going to tell them now to start chasing. I know I don't need to have an appointment, I just asked for them to CC me on the referral and I haven't seen anything and it's really stressing me out trying to get it all done
